The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 3 Howrah youths drown in Mysore 
                                                                                                               3 Howrah youths drown in Mysore 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Three youths from Howrah drowned in a lake near Mysore on Sunday after their boat overturned. While two bodies have been recovered, divers hadnt found the third body till late on Monday.         
	Aftab Alam, 22, Mohammad Jawed, 22 and Mohammad Azad, 19  residents of Basiruddin Munsi Lane in Howrah, had gone to Karnataka two years ago to work in garment factories.         
	We have learnt that the three boys went for an outing to Mysore with some other friends on Sunday. They decided to take a boat ride and the boat overturned in the middle of the lake. Though three of their friends swam to safety, the trio drowned, said a neighbour of Alam in Howrah.         
	On Sunday night, the youths who survived the mishap rang up the families of Alam, Jawed and Azad to inform them about the tragedy. The bodies of Aftab and Jawed have been recovered but Azads body was yet to be found.         
	Howrah district officials contacted the district collector of Mandai district in Tamil Nadu and sought his help in the matter. The family members of the three youths left for Karnataka on Monday morning, the neighbour added.         
	Khalil Ahmed, the Howrah district magistrate, said the district authorities were a waiting a detailed report from the Karnataka government. According to primary reports three Howrah youths who worked in a garment factory in Karnataka have drowned while boating in a lake on the Karnataka and Tamil Nadu border, he added. He said the district administration would help the families to bring back the bodies to Howrah.                                                                                                                                                                            
